}} The '2005â06 season' was Colchester United's eighth consecutive season in the
third tier of English football. The season ended in success with Colchester's
first ever promotion into the second tier of English football when they finished
2nd in League One. In addition, they had good cup runs in the FA Cup, being
knocked out by then Premier League champions Chelsea in the 5th round, and
finished as area finalists in the LDV Vans Trophy.
